  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="poetry">
        <head rend="noCount" rendition="#center">TO GENERAL LOYD. THE HUMBLE PETITION OF THE OLD ELMS AT THE WEST END OF WOOLWICH BARRACKS (1800–1).
        <note type="headnote" place="foot" resp="editors">Bloomfield does not date the poem, but the building of a new barrack block at Woolwich to
          which it refers was completed in 1802.</note></head>
        <lg type="stanza">
          <l rendition="#indent3">WE soldiers of the western hill,</l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">Turn’d up with nature’s cheerful green; </l>
          <l rendition="#indent3">Since our young stems came here to drill,</l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">What revolutions have we seen!</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="stanza">
          <l rendition="#indent3">We’ve witness’d many a gallant launch;</l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">We’ve bow’d to many a gay review; </l>
          <l rendition="#indent3">And still, we’re like your Honour—stanch;</l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">And humbly plead our cause with you. </l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="stanza">
          <l rendition="#indent3">Oh! shall we be condemn’d to die, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">Whilst your vast barracks raise our wonder;</l>
          <l rendition="#indent3">Whose deep foundations come so nigh, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">They cut our very roots asunder?</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="stanza">
          <l rendition="#indent3">We’ve stood through many a stormy night, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">Ay! long before your men were born, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent3">Who braved the thunder of the fight, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">And toils and terrors laugh’d to scorn. </l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="stanza">
          <l rendition="#indent3">How grateful is the summer shade, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">How bleak this hill would look without us; </l>
          <l rendition="#indent3">Here let the vows of love be made, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">And blooming maids still flock about us.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="stanza">
          <l rendition="#indent3">Let us remain the spot to show, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">(Though honour bids a nation arm), </l>
          <l rendition="#indent3">Where grazing kine were wont to low, </l>
          <l rendition="#indent4">And once was found a peaceful farm.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
